column2: Can you beat Spore WITHOUT Evolving?
column7:
Hello there ladies and gentlemen today something magical is about to happen today in todays video! The Spiffing Brit today attempts to play the 2008 classical game that is Spore. A game so unique that it took miracle video game god Will Wright to create a perfect game that inspired a generation of gamers before the release of minecraft. Welcome to Spore! Spore is a evolution game where you start as a single cell object and as you eat, you gain DNA and abilities! The only issue is today we will be seeing if you can beat spore without evolving! That's right the spore no evolution challenge is going to be incredible! It will once and for all prove that spore is a perfectly balanced game which can for some reason be beaten by bypassing the core gameplay loop of evolving creatures to gain new abilities. And for some reason we are able to go from cell stage to creature stage to tribal stage to civilization stage and finally the space stage!

So today I show you how to Break the game by beating it without evolving! It is one very exciting video game challenge! So lets play spore!

column2: Dragon Age Origins - ALL COMPANIONS DIE in the WORST Playthrough Ever
column7:
So this video is going to be a wild ride.  Today we‚Äôre going to explore the worst playthrough of Dragon Age Origins ever, where the Warden makes the worst decisions and gets every single one of his companions killed throughout the course of the game.  Now there are a couple of characters‚Ä¶ really only one character who has enough plot armor to prevent them from dying during the course of the main story.  And that is Morrigan, but we are going to do our best to rid ourselves of the witch as well.  So grab some popcorn, maybe an iced coffee and buckle up.  Because this is a crazy one.

DRAGON AGE ORIGINS - MORRIGAN KILLS WYNNE
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mg05MSv6hXk

DRAGON AGE ORIGINS - WHAT HAPPENS IF YOU BETRAY MORRIGAN
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=S9KeBdu8hTo

DRAGON AGE ORIGINS - WHAT HAPPENS IF YOU KILL OGHREN
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3UbZ2HrtPAI

0:00 Introduction
1:47 Creating Bald Warden, An Evil Blood Mage
2:19 RIP Doge
2:59 So... Ostagar Went Well, Eh?
3:22 Sten Dies in Lothering
5:12 Redcliffe Village Destroyed
6:01 Selling Connor's Soul for Blood Magic
7:06 Wynne Dies and the Circle is Destroyed
8:15 Betraying Morrigan
9:22 Recruit Zevran & Shale.  Side with the Werewolves.
9:58 Poison Urn and Kill Leliana :(
11:46 Siding with Branka and Killing Shale
12:41 Alistair HATES Bald Warden
13:18 Killing Zevran
14:25 Landsmeet
15:56 Anora is Queen. Loghain is Warden. Alistair is Dead.
19:23 Killing Oghren
20:17 Refusing the Dark Ritual
21:00 Battle of Denerim
21:57 Loghain Dies to Slay the Archdemon
23:46 The Most PATHETIC Post-Coronation Ceremony
24:43 Killing Morrigan? (Witch Hunt DLC)

In most video games you play as the hero - and that is technically the case in Dragon Age Origins.  I mean you do earn the title ‚ÄúHero of Ferelden‚Äù by the end of the game.  But I have been consistently floored with how evil Bioware lets you be in this game.  You can act completely selfish, make the worst decisions and even kill your own companions to become a supreme jagoff.

So as an experiment, I wanted to push the envelope and see if I could get all of my companions killed in a single playthrough.  And to my surprise, it is absolutely possible.  We‚Äôre just going to cover the base game of Dragon Age Origins in this video, as well as the Witch Hunt DLC briefly at the end.

Creating a truly evil bastard starts in character creation.  We need our Warden to look the part in order to fully immerse ourselves in this character.  For class we‚Äôre going to choose mage, so that we can become a blood mage later on.  And for our look we‚Äôll go bald and add some facial tattoos.  Ehhhh.  You see this man, you know bad things are about to happen.  You see this man, you turn and run.

column2: RimWorld: The Good Guy Run [500% Difficulty, No Pause, No Warcrimes | Part 1]
column7:
Is RimWorld still RimWorld without warcrimes? We're going to find out in this playthrough! Let's see if the old saying is true - do good guys always finish last?

Full playthrough is played on Losing Is Fun set to +500% difficulty without pausing against Randy Random. No additional mods to help the good guys was added.

Hope you enjoy this RimWorld Challenge Run!

HAIR : Dyed my hair as part of a promise for the community hitting a fundraising charity goal. As a group, we raised $85,000 for Doctors Without Borders! Here's my part in the charity event: https://www.twitch.tv/videos/1226726962

---------- DETAILS ----------
This playthrough was recorded LIVE on Twitch. As such, Adam is speaking with chat throughout. Videos without chat will be listed as 'Youtube Exclusive'. This is the ENTIRE playthrough, so there will be some episodes in which not much happens, that's just the nature of unedited RimWorld.

*No Pause - Adam is using a mod that disables pause in every portion of the game. This means it is impossible for him to pause with a  key press and the game will not pause during events or trade, making things much more difficult.

** Losing is Fun set to +500% is the hardest difficulty in unmodded RimWorld

column2: Can You Beat SHADOW OF MORDOR With Only Wraith Powers?
column7:
I find your lack of faith...disturbing.

Shadow of Mordor is a great game, and has lots of stealth, combat, and "magic" options. So what if we took away 2/3 of that? After all, it's kinda silly that a ghost can use physical weapons.

Time to banish Mordor to the shadow realm.
